      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KEEP ROLLING (3) ran well two back scoring a Grade 5 win in 29.68 then out of the placings at Geelong latest but returns to a course where he has performed well. Will find this more suitable and can atone. PAW ZURI (1) produced an impressive win last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 6 lengths (29.80) at this track. Has definite claims again. CONSIGLIERE (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.75 lengths at Sandown in a handy 29.47 beating Dr. Babette. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. GALENTO (5) cannot be ruled out.",
